reviews.text: We love their pizzas and pasta. We missed them so much when they had to move into another space in the same mall. It was worth the wait. Still as amazing as ever. Though we do take out, they new space is bright and cheery with some funky murals and neon lights.

I got two subs. A chicken parm and a steak and cheese. Extra cheese on both, onions and mushrooms on the steak and cheese.  It was over $32. The chicken parm was sour and acidic tasting, like they put the sauce in the fridge while it was still hot. both subs had very thin foil wrapped around them that easily crumbled apart when I unwrapped it.  I think I might have swallowed a piece of foil by accident.. I would not recommend this place. I have had a couple of pizzas there since they reopened, and they were very mediocre.

First off, I will recommend Victoria‚Äôs in general - friendly service, good people, good ‚Äúhouse of pizza‚Äù style pizza, offer delivery, and good option for serving a party‚Ä¶ Nothing special, but gets the job done
BUT I‚Äôm writing this review to warn you off their roast beef. I‚Äôve never had an out-and-out BAD sub from Victoria‚Äôs (mediocre, yes. Good, yes.) until TODAY!  I got a roast beef sub today that was absolutely not worth the money! It won‚Äôt make you sick, but please don‚Äôt order it. It‚Äôs very brown. Very thick. Very stringy.  Not at all the thinly sliced, succulent pink roast beef you‚Äôre craving (and expect!) In addition there was not a lot of meat on the roll. (Although the meat was so off putting, I guess in the end that was a good thing) Just stick with pizza or an Italian sub when you come here. An absolute NO on the roast beef! (Here‚Äôs a photo of half my sub - I‚Äôd regrettably just eaten the first half) I paid $11 for a small and this was it‚Ä¶ yikes!!!)

Service was mediocre at best. Staff seemed miserable, did not get greeted by anyone. I was hoping the food would turn my review around but sadly it did not. The fries were way too well done and didn‚Äôt have a drop of salt on them. The steak and cheese was average at best. I do not recommend.
Stop in to pick up lunch. Place looks great which the prices reflect.

detailedReviews.author: Marisa A Agostino (Ree)
detailedReviews.text: I did a takeout/delivery order it was my first time ordering since they just reopened after their remodel and everything was great! I really enjoyed the apple walnut salad that I got it was delicious and I will for sure be ordering it again. We also ordered the thanksgiving turkey sub and that was really good as well. The delivery time was good they told me an hour but it was here before then and the delivery driver guy was very pleasant and I made sure he was tipped well too. Overall I would say that they are a good staple to have in town again and it's great  that they are so local to me for when I want to order out or just looking to get something quick. Definitely give them a try! Thanks Victoria's Sub and Pizza for the delicious food and service.

detailedReviews.author: Kelsey Olander
detailedReviews.text: Incredibly disappointed by the attitude of staff and the way our pizza was packaged at the new location. Google states that the restaurant closes at 9PM and I received a phone call at 8:10PM saying they were closing and that we had to come get our food. My husband arrived at 8:15 PM and the entrance lights were off and it was clear that we were ‚Äúinconveniencing‚Äù staff when they rushed our food to us. Do not treat customers this way when a shop clearly states in multiple places that it doesn‚Äôt close for another 45 minutes. To add insult to injury, two of our slices were completely inedible as they shoved our pizza into a box that was too small and the pizza was completely folded over on itself. When you‚Äôre paying $40 for mozzarella sticks and one pizza, I feel we‚Äôre deserved just a tad bit more respect. Very disappointed with new changes.

detailedReviews.author: Jerome Crowley
detailedReviews.text: Professional and courteous

detailedReviews.author: Melanie Roake
detailedReviews.text: I only have wonderful things to say about victorias! They are all so kind and we are so happy they are back! My family and work family missed them so much! We are thrilled to have them back! Still the best around!

detailedReviews.author: Aislyn Arnone
detailedReviews.text: We‚Äôve been eagerly waiting for Victoria‚Äôs to reopen after their move and renovations. They officially reopened on Thursday, and we couldn‚Äôt wait to place a takeout order tonight. The new space is impressive‚Äîbright, clean, and incredibly welcoming. The staff were warm and friendly, and the food was even better than before. We ordered two pizzas (cheese and pepperoni) and two subs (steak and cheese, and hamburger), and everything was fantastic! Highly recommend!

detailedReviews.text: I usually get delivery. This time I picked up some pans for a party. The meatballs were delicious and plentiful. The lasagna thick and cheesy. The salad fresh with a great assortment of dressings.  I will get catering again.

detailedReviews.text: Was visiting friends who live in the area and we had been shopping and decided to grab supper to go. We ordered 3 dinners to go and we sat and we sat. A lot of people who came in after us got their meals before us. After 15 minutes my friends husband enquired about how much longer. The response from the cashier was: ‚Äú oh the dinners ‚Äú .  So we knew we‚Äôd been forgotten but they didn‚Äôt want to admit it. After another 15 or 20 minutes we finally got our food. It was very good but too big of a serving of onion rings with meal. I‚Äôm not sure my friends will be back as customers or not.

He was coughing and sneezing, while delivering the food to the people in the restaurant, the Man of staff that is responsible to make sure that the food is delivered safely without tampering is infecting everything that he served with whatever  he had for an illness. Disgusting.

strengthsPerceived: Customers appreciate the timely delivery service, as evidenced by the on-time delivery for a birthday party and faster-than-expected delivery times. - Boostly marketing services can amplify this
The new location's ambiance, featuring bright and cheery decor with funky murals and neon lights, enhances the dining experience. - social media marketing can showcase this strength
The friendly and professional staff, including a committed owner, contribute to a welcoming and enjoyable dining experience. - review management can highlight this positive aspect
improvementOpportunities: Negative reviews and reputation issues, particularly around poor service, food quality, and misleading operating hours - review management can address this concern
